This paper is about a novel architecture for 3D convolutional neural networks for segmentation, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses memory efficiency, which is a common concern in machine learning and deep learning, making categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) likely as well. Finally, the paper deals with volumetric image segmentation, which is a subfield of medical imaging (cs.MM).
